The paper deals with the design and decoding of space-time block codes, which are commonly used in wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses interference cancellation techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper proposes a design criterion for achieving full diversity, which is related to the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed decoding algorithm, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). Finally, the paper proposes a complexity-performance-rate tradeoff, which is related to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
